Our teammate S pyo  (Streptococcus pyogenes if you're nasty) (who we invited to work with us instead of working against us) hugging a tree, as best they can, since they don't have arms. (I the photographer also hugged a tree). 
This is a rare and beautiful can-dy tree - it is generating canned hints, that S pyo is collecting for us while diligently practicing their semaphore.
